args: Hey, Orion. I heard today's job\nis a bit special?
Indeed. Ever since I started working out of\nthe Halidom, my reputation has soared.
And today I have a direct request\nfrom the daughter of a noble!
Well, that certainly sounds important.\nAre you sure you want me along?
Our dear Cleo insisted upon it, actually.\nShe seems to think I'm going to muck up\nthe worksâ€”which HURTS, may I add?
Heh. I remember her saying your form had\nbeen a bit...lacking lately on account of\nhow much you've been trying to hold back.

I can't believe you all have so little faith
in me. I'm a professional! I won't foul
up a job simply because I'm changing
the way I approach my clients.
And today, I prove this to all!
Ah. It looks like we're here.
Good afternoon. Are you the two\nwho will be escorting me?
Indeed, milady. I am Orion, and this is\nmy assistant, {player_name}.
I've HEARD of you! You preside over\nthe Halidom, do you not?
Ha ha ha! Yes, as you can see,\nyou are in the safest of hands.
It's just a short way to town now.\nHow are you feeling, milady?
I'm all right at the moment, but I hear\nthis area is particularly dangerous.
Supposedly there's a band of thieves in\nthe area that has enslaved fiends to their\nwills. Please do be careful!
Be they fiend or thief, none will lay a\nhandâ€”or slimy clawâ€”on you this day!
Ah, but once we ARE safely in town,\nI would love it if you wouldâ€”
I m-mean, I would love it if you wooould...
Watch me dance with fiends!\nYes, that's it. A...fiend...dance.
Is that right? What a most singular\ntalent, sir.
Ha ha! I'd not be a professional if I\ncouldn't handle a blade or dance witâ€”
Bwaaa ha ha! This 'ere's a dangerous\nplace what for rich ladies!
So it seems. Stay behind meâ€”\nand stay close.
I'll not let them hurt you.\n...{player_name}?
Cor, these two got some life in 'em\nso they do! Get em, boys!
Ugh! There's so many of them...\nI need help!
(Something is off here. They don't seem\nto be trying to abduct her at all.)
(Well, no time to ponder it.\nI must protect my charge!)
Bwaaa ha ha! Eat this, fancy man!
Gah... I'm g-glad I could protect...you...\nAre you...well...milady?
You took a pretty serious blow for us\nback there, Orion. You going to be okay?
As long as the two of you are safe,\nnothing else matters.
Now then, we're almost at our destination.\nWe can talk there.
I'm glad I was able to see to your wounds.
And I am glad to finish the job\nwith you unharmed.
I'm so sorry you were hurt for my sake.
The reward you were promised simply isn't\nenough to cover what you went through.\nIs there anything else I can do?
...I know! I will hold a party in your honor!
It is the least I can do to thank the two\nof you for what you have done. Oh,\nbut you simply MUST come!
I wouldn't miss it for the world.\nHowever...
Perhaps we could enjoy a rendezvous of\ndreams just amongst ourselves instead?
Orion! That's the kind of thing\nyou're not supposed to say anymore!
Blast! I spoke without thought again!\n...Are you angry with me, milady?

However, I'm afraid I might be a bit...
nervous with a guest list of just two,
so I would prefer the party to be
something of a more grand affair.
Is that all right with you?
I shall do whatever you like, milady.
(Whew! That was close.\nI almost ruined everything...)
I am quite looking forward to it.
